baseSetSize.description: Number of cards in the set. Will default to `totalSetSize` if not available. Note that Wizards sometimes prints extra cards beyond the set size into promos or supplemental products.

block.description: Block name the set was in.

boosterV3.description: The card rarity contents of a typical booster pack.

cards.description: List of cards in this set.

codeV3.description: Alternate set code Wizards uses for a select few duel deck sets. (If there is not an alternate set code, this field is omitted.)

isFoilOnly.description: Set available only in foil. (If false, it is usually omitted.)

isOnlineOnly.description: Set available online only. Can be true or false. (If false, it is usually omitted.)

keyruneCode.description: The matching keyrune code for keyrune.css image icons.

mcmName.description: The Magic Card Market set name.

mcmId.description: The Magic Card Market set id.

mtgoCode.description: Set code for the set as it appears on Magic: The Gathering Online.

releaseDate.description: Date of release for the set.

tcgplayerGroupId.description: Group ID of the set on TCGPlayer.

tokens.description: Tokens available to the set. See the {{token}} structure.

totalSetSize.description: Total number of cards in the set, including promos and related supplemental products.

translations.description: Translated set name by language. See the {{translations}} structure.
